<p align="center"><b>TERMS AND CONDITIONS 
FOR THE ORDNANCE SURVEY ‘BEST PHOTOGRAPH’ AND 
‘BAG THE MOST ORDNANCE SURVEY GRID SQUARES’ COMPETITIONS IN ASSOCIATION 
WITH GEOGRAPH</b></p>

<p align="center"><b>(the "Competitions")</b></p>
<h3 align="justify"><b>Promoter</b></h3>

<ol type="1">
  <li>The promoter of the Competitions 
  is The Secretary of State for Communities and Local Government acting 
  through Ordnance Survey of Romsey Road, Maybush, Southampton, Hampshire 
  SO16 4GU, England ("<b>Ordnance Survey</b>").</li>
</ol>
<h3 align="justify"><b>Eligibility to the 
Competitions</b></h3>
<ol type="1" start="2">
  <li>Entry is only open to UK permanent 
  residents aged 18 and under in full time education.</li>
  <li>Employees of Ordnance Survey 
  or Geograph Project Limited (of 27 Mons Avenue, Baldock, Hertfordshire, 
  SG7 6JX, England ("<b>Geograph</b>") and/or their immediate families, 
  agents, households or anyone connected with the competitions are ineligible 
  to enter. </li>

  <li>Ordnance Survey reserves the 
  right to require you to prove that you are eligible for entry under 
  these terms and conditions.  If the winner of a prize was ineligible 
  for entry in a Competition, Ordnance Survey may award the prize to someone 
  else.</li>
  <li>The use of unfair advantages 
  (such as hacking into the Website) or collaborative practices may result 
  in your disqualification.</li>
</ol>
<h3 align="justify"><b>How to enter the 
Competitions</b></h3>
<ol type="1" start="6">
  <li>The Competitions will both 
  operate on the Geograph website at the following URL address: <a href="http://schools.geograph.org.uk" target="_blank">http://schools.geograph.org.uk</a> 
  (the '<b>Website</b>').  The Competitions both start on 1 April 
  2008.</li>

  <li>To enter either Competition 
  you must upload at least one photograph that you have taken to the Website.  
  The photograph should be of one of the main geographical features within 
  an Ordnance Survey map’s one kilometre square grid (e.g. a close range 
  photograph of a building together with some of its surroundings, physical 
  landscape, geology or flora and fauna).  Any photograph you upload 
  must comply with the guidance on the Website at <a href="http://schools.geograph.org.uk/article/Geograph-or-supplemental" target="_blank"><u>http://schools.geograph.org.uk<WBR>/article/Geograph-or-supplement<WBR>al</u></a> and <a href="http://schools.geograph.org.uk/faq.php" target="_blank">http://schools.geograph.org.uk<WBR>/faq.php</a>.  
  For example, the longest side of the photograph should be at least 480 
  pixels long and any image should be shown as a natural image i.e. as 
  a human would see it.  Please avoid digitally altering the image to 
  add dates or text, for example.  Similarly, please turn off any 
  date stamping performed by a camera.  Feel free, however, to adjust 
  the brightness or contrast of the image and/or to crop it.</li>
  <li>In order to upload a photograph, 
  you must register on the Website by entering your name, email address 
  and a password on the relevant section of the Website.  You will 
  need to confirm your registration by clicking on the link in the email 
  sent to you.  Registration is free. </li>
  <li>You should also include a 
  short description of your photograph in accordance with the style guide 
  at <a href="http://schools.geograph.org.uk/help/style" target="_blank"><u>http://schools.geograph.org.uk<WBR>/help/style</u></a>.</li>

  <li>When uploading a photograph, 
  the last web page of the submission process will contain a box for you 
  to enter the Mapping News competition code.  Please ensure that 
  you enter the competition code 'MN1' into this box. </li>
  <li>Entries by email, post or 
  fax will not be accepted.  Uploading your photograph to the Website 
  is the only way to enter the Competitions.</li>
  <li>All photographs to enter 
  the Competitions must be uploaded by midnight on the closing date of 
  30 September 2008.</li>
  <li><b>By entering 
  either of the Competitions, you are confirming that you have read, understood 
  and agree to be bound by these terms and conditions and the 
  Website’s terms of use, which are available to review here: </b><a href="http://schools.geograph.org.uk/help/terms" target="_blank"><b><u>http://schools.geograph.org.uk<WBR>/help/terms</u></b></a><b> </b></li>
  <li><b>You can make as many entries 
  into either Competition as you like.</b></li>

  <li><b>Please note: for the 
  ‘best photograph’ competition, although a grid square may already 
  have photographs uploaded for it, you can always upload more photographs.</b></li>
</ol>
