<h3 align="justify"><b>Prizes</b></h3>
<ol type="1" start="17">

  <li>Each competition has one 
  prize of a digital camera worth £150.  [The cameras will include a 
  2Gb memory card] </li>
  <li>The prize is as stated and 
  is non-exchangeable and non-transferable.  There is no cash or 
  other alternative to the prize.  Ordnance Survey reserves the right 
  to substitute a prize for an alternative prize at its discretion. </li>
</ol>
<h3 align="justify"><b>How we select the 
winner of the ‘best photograph’ 
competition</b></h3>
<ol type="1" start="19">
  <li>The winner of the ‘best 
  photograph’ competition will be the person who, in the opinion of 
  the panel of three judges, uploads the best photograph to the Website.  
  The photograph will be judged according to the following criteria, the:</li>
  </ol>
<ul>
<ul type="DISC">

  <li>quality and composition of 
  the photograph;</li>
</ul>
<ul type="DISC">
  <li>accuracy of the exposure used 
  in the photograph; and</li>
  <li>way in which the photograph 
  represents the contents of the one kilometre square grid.</li>
  </ul>
</ul>
<ol type="1" start="20">
  <li>The panel of judges will 
  select the winner from all eligible, properly submitted, entries received.  
  The judges’ names will be available on request.  </li>

</ol>
<h3 align="justify"><b>How we select the 
winner of the ‘Bag the most grid squares’ competition</b></h3>
<ol type="1" start="21">
  <li>The winner of the ‘Bag 
  the most grid squares’ competition will be the person who uploads 
  the most photographs that are the first photograph to be uploaded for 
  a one kilometre square grid between the start and the end of the competition 
  period (i.e. between 1 April 2008 and 30 September 2008).  Grid 
  squares which do not yet have any photographs uploaded for them are 
  represented in a bright green colour on the map on the Website.  
  Grid squares that already have at least one photograph uploaded for 
  them are shown in red.</li>
</ol>
